ountertops Countertop Makeover Kitchen Countertops";s:3:"alt";s:9:"pinterest";s:3:"url";s:76:"https://i.pinimg.com/originals/ba/cf/90/bacf900869fece01cfe740c0135f58dd.jpg";s:5:"thumb";s:90:"https://encrypted-tbn0.gstatic.com/images?q=tbn:ANd9GcQsUhl_RhqGu1e5xleGdjP9t8DKFrvSZHxgtw";s:8:"filetype";s:3:"jpg";s:5:"width";i:427;s:6:"height";i:640;s:6:"source";s:48:"https://www.pinterest.com/pin/52917364346044288/";s:6:"domain";s:17:"www.pinterest.com";}}s:9:"sentences";a:53:{i:0;s:28:"May 19 2016 by devisingsite.";i:1;s:95:"Chair duets is when you sit next to a partner and use a series of improvised contact movements.";i:2;s:99:"In order to successfully achieve a chair duet there has to be some sort of call and response sense.";i:3;s:107:"The idea of Chair Duets is to build a story through movement and ultimately create a working scene from it.";i:4;s:98:"According to Frantic Assembly a story will naturally develop after adding meaning to the movement.";i:5;s:129:"Chair duets were developed by Frantic Assembly to help establish the relationship between two or more of the characters on stage.";i:6;s:223:"When developing our own in a workshop our characters didnt have an established relationship therefore the movements we decided to use in the duet allowed the audience to decide the complexity of our relationship themselves.";i:7;s:77:"Duet Acting involves two people two chairs and in some jurisdictions a table.";i:8;s:54:"The furniture is supplied in each room of competition.";i:9;s:126:"Time limits vary but generally each acting pair performs an eight- to twelve-minute scene typically using only two characters.";i:10;s:56:"Frantic Assembly Book of Devising Theatre - Chair Duets.";i:11;s:60:"If playback doesnt begin shortly try restarting your device.";i:12;s:88:"Videos you watch may be added to the TVs watch history and influence TV recommendations.";i:13;s:142:"The 19 undergraduates in her class spent four sessions studying the concept of chair duets and creating and filming their own original pieces.";i:14;s:133:"They were inspired by the Chair Duets Challenge set forth by Frantic Assembly an innovative drama troupe based in the United Kingdom.";i:15;s:160:"The chair duet has become for us a way to capture the ups and downs of first dates and relationships in a very simple but physical and visually interesting way.";i:16;s:76:"Frantic Assembly 2009 Frantic Assembly Book of Devising Theatre Chair Duets.";i:17;s:287:"Chair duets working together letting the movement create the character Dance Drama Devised Drama Curious Incident Love-song Othello DV8 Physical Theatre Dance Drama- Lifts grips leans spins Using dance to tell the story Enter Achilles John Can We Talk About This To Be Straight With you.";i:18;s:101:"A theatre company devised a play centred on some elderly characters recalling their past experiences.";i:19;s:67:"The set was simple consisting of just four chairs and a mirrorball.";i:20;s:16:"The chairs were.";i:21;s:135:"Picking Oose uses everyday movements like picking a piece of fluff from somebodys jumper adjusting their collar or touching their hand.";i:22;s:122:"This can then be developed sometimes by incorporating other devising techniques to tell a story and create a relationship.";i:23;s:126:"This piece shows us just what you can do with a couple of everyday objects a couple of simple rules and a vibrant imagination.";i:24;s:29:"The WISS Grade 9 Dance and D.";i:25;s:89:"First Run Game Over Chair Duets Documenting the journey of our multimedia movement piece.";i:26;s:97:"This is the first piece of material we have generated inspired by Frantic Assemblys chair duetsT.";i:27;s:168:"A duet is a musical composition for two performers in which the performers have equal importance to the piece often a composition involving two singers or two pianists.";i:28;s:119:"It differs from a harmony as the performers take turns performing a solo section rather than performing simultaneously.";i:29;s:108:"A piece performed by two 